# Hybrid Requirements Preprocessing Datasets

This project is a Streamlit application for preprocessing, extracting, classifying and merging software requirements from different file formats.

## Objective

The system helps transform raw documents (TXT, PDF, CSV, XLSX, images) into a structured dataset of requirements, ready for analysis, classification and validation.

## Main features

1. Requirement extraction
   - Reads TXT, PDF, CSV, XLSX, XLS and image files
   - Removes noise and metadata from documents
   - Extracts sentences that look like requirements

2. Requirement classification (ISO/IEC/IEEE 25010)
   - Classifies requirements as FR and NFR
   - Can use subclasses such as Performance, Usability, Reliability, Security, Maintainability, Compatibility and Portability

3. Dataset merging
   - Combines multiple files into a single dataset
   - Normalises columns and text
   - Exports the result as CSV

4. Hybrid LLM support
   - Cloud mode: OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini
   - Local mode: LM Studio, Ollama

---

## Project structure

- `app.py` — main Streamlit interface
- `pipeline/extract.py` — requirement extraction pipeline
- `pipeline/classify.py` — requirement classification pipeline
- `pipeline/merge.py` — dataset merging pipeline
- `pipeline/loader.py` — file loading and normalisation utilities
- `core/llm.py` — LLM provider abstraction
- `core/cache.py` — LLM response caching
- `core/config.py` — prompts and system constants
- `myutils/text.py` — text cleaning and parsing helpers
- `myutils/io.py` — safe file reading

---

## How to run

### 1. Create a virtual environment

```powershell
cd G:\preprocessing
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

### 2. Install dependencies

```powershell
pip install streamlit pandas openai google-genai pytesseract pdf2image pillow fitz
```

### 3. Run the application

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m streamlit run app.py
```

The application will be available at:

```text
http://localhost:8501
```

---

## Interface modes

- `Auto` — runs extraction and classification in sequence
- `Extraction` — generates only the extracted requirement list
- `Classification` — classifies extracted requirements or directly uses uploaded files
- `Merge` — merges files or uses already classified results

---

## Supported formats

- `.txt`
- `.pdf`
- `.csv`
- `.xlsx`, `.xls`
- `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.tiff`, `.tif`

---

## Important notes

- Extraction depends on text cleaning and heuristics to identify real requirements.
- Classification uses LLMs and may vary depending on the chosen model.
- The project is still under refinement and can be improved with automated tests, schema validation and more robust caching.

